Day 19 â€“ CSS Transitions and Hover

Transitions create smooth effects when properties change.
:hover applies style changes when mouse is over an element.
Example:

button {
  background-color: blue;
  color: white;
  padding: 10px;
  transition: 0.5s;
}
button:hover {
  background-color: red;
  transform: scale(1.1);
}


Transitions and hover effects improve interactivity and UX.
